            "answer_text": "There are many ways to say \u2018it's ok\u2019 in japanese. You can say okay as ( \u30aa\u30c3\u30b1) / (okk\u00e9). The script which is used here is katakana which is used to pronounce foreign words. Or you can say okay as ( \u3060\u3044\u3058\u3087\u3046\u3076\u3067\u3059) / (daijoubu) . The script which is used here is Hiragana which is used to pronounce domestic words. Daijoubu means Alright too. Or you can say okay as ( \u3051\u3063\u3053\u3046\u3067\u3059) / ( kekkou desu ). It means no thanks. Hope it helps. ",
